benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods/{paymentMethodId}/setDefault - Set the default payment method

covered: Valid Request: The tests cover successful updates with required and optional parameters (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05).
Non-Existing Resource: Error scenarios for non-existent accounts/methods and mismatches (TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC16).
Authorization/Headers: Tests for missing header (TC11) and unauthorized (TC12) are present.
Query Parameter Handling: payAllUnpaidInvoices, pluginProperty, and extra params (TC02, TC03, TC14, TC15, TC25).
Concurrency: Concurrency scenario (TC22) ensures a single default is applied and state remains consistent.
Error Handling/Service Availability: Cases for service unavailability (TC13) and timeout/504/503 (TC18), as well as invalid inputs (TC19, TC23).
Regression: Regression tests for old bugs (TC20, TC21).
Performance: Large/unpaid invoices processing and acceptable response time (TC17).
Edge case coverage: min/max UUID values and max pluginProperty length (TC16, TC15).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests cover rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Caching/Headers: No tests examining cache headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Idempotence edge-case: No explicit test for repeated identical updates when the default is already set.
Edge-case: invalid header values or unusual characters in createdBy header beyond SQL injection (TC19) could be expanded.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests and verify handling of bursts of PUT /setDefault requests.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and validate cache invalidation semantics.
Add an explicit idempotence test for re-setting the same default payment method and ensure no unintended side effects.
Expand header/input validation tests (e.g., unusual characters in createdBy, and more pluginProperty value validations).
Consider a focused test for the minimal/maximum payload edge cases and for server timeout handling under slow downstream dependencies.
